  <roomsDescription><![CDATA[<p><strong>Double Rooms</strong> <strong>on Half Board </strong>are around 20m² and sleep two people. These rooms can take a cot. These are part of a special offer on half board only, on a first come first served basis.</p>
<p><strong>Triple Rooms</strong> <strong>on Full Board </strong>are around 21-24m² and sleep two to three people. This room can be made up as a double and one single bed, or as three single beds. </p>
<p><strong>Quad Rooms on Full Board</strong> are around 24m², sleep two to four people (maximum two adults, two children under 11 years old) with a double bed and bunk beds for two children. Children under 6 years old cannot sleep on the top bunk bed.</p>
<p>Single occupancy rooms are available on request, for a supplement. Rooms must be fully occupied during high season dates (Christmas, New Year, French February school holidays and Easter). In low season rooms maybe allocated according to the number of occupants. </p>
<p>Free upgrade to all inclusive for departures 22nd, 29th Mar &amp; 5th Apr 25 is valid for all room types.</p>
<p><strong>Bedroom facilities</strong></p>
<ul>
<li>Twin or double beds (please specify at time of booking)</li>
<li>TV</li>
<li>Bathroom with shower</li>
<li>Separate WC</li>
<li>Heated towel rail</li>
<li>Toiletries</li>
<li>Towels </li>
<li>Hairdryer </li>
<li>Free Wi-Fi</li>
<li>Daily housekeeping</li>
</ul>
<p> </p>]]></roomsDescription>
